This paper is about information extraction (IE) using distant labeling, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques for reducing noise in the training data, which is a common problem in machine learning (ML) and data mining (DM), suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions using document structure and analyzing sections, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and search engines, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses augmenting a large corpus with coupling constraints, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and knowledge representation, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category.
